# Walkthrough: Sprint P0-1C — Regression Runtime Closure

This sprint focused on closing all runtime regressions identified in previous cycles, ensuring 100% UI stability and robust error handling.

## 1. Resolved Critical UI Crashes

We eliminated several White Screen of Death (WSOD) scenarios by implementing defensive guards and safe fallbacks.

- **Employee List**: Fixed a crash caused by missing pagination data.
- **Security Settings**: Handled undefined password policy and session timeout properties.
- **Integrations**: Safely handled unknown or malformed integration names.
- **Notifications**: Ensured all toggles (SMS, In-App, Email) use stable boolean states.

## 2. Help & Support Recovery

Recovered the Help and Support experience by aligning Gateway routing and fixing Backend model exports.

- **Help Search**: Aliased `/api/help/search` to the internal backend method and fixed gateway routing.
- **Support Tickets**: Resolved 500 errors by exporting the help schema in [models/index.ts](file:///d:/%D9%85%D8%B4%D8%B1%D9%88%D8%B9/14-2-2026/2026-2-13/smart_performance_system/server/data/models/index.ts) and implementing robust user ID resolution (email to UUID).
- **Graceful Failure**: The UI now displays stable, user-friendly messages if the support backend is temporarily unavailable, rather than crashing.

## 3. Service Resilience & Optimization

Improved the overall system performance and reduced developer console noise.

- **Profile Data Noise**: Implemented an early exit in [ProfileDataAdapter](file:///d:/%D9%85%D8%B4%D8%B1%D9%88%D8%B9/14-2-2026/2026-2-13/smart_performance_system/client/src/services/resources/profileDataAdapter.ts#158-621). If an employee ID is not found (404), secondary analytics requests are automatically canceled.
- **WebSocket Stability**: Optimized [websocket.ts](file:///d:/%D9%85%D8%B4%D8%B1%D9%88%D8%B9/14-2-2026/2026-2-13/smart_performance_system/client/src/services/websocket.ts) to use exponential backoff for reconnections and silenced transient error logs to keep the console clean.
- **SMS Notifications**: Fixed controlled/uncontrolled state warnings in the settings interface.

## Verification Proof

### Browser Walkthrough Results
- **Employees Page**: Stable (No crashes).
- **Non-existent Employee (404)**: Shows clear error, no excessive network traffic.
- **Settings Tabs**: All tabs (Security, Integrations, Notifications) load perfectly.
- **Help Search**: Functional search results.
- **Support Tickets**: Error message is stable and non-disruptive.

